photos.caption: A male Vermilion Flycatcher on a bare branch, brilliant scarlet contrasting with dark gray wings.
An immature female Vermilion Flycatcher perched on a metal rail, showing streaked breast and buffy flanks.
A male Vermilion Flycatcher in mid-flight, brilliant scarlet body and dark wings spread against clear blue sky.
A Great Kiskadee bursting out of a swimming pool in an explosion of water droplets after a plunge-dive.

A Colombian Chachalaca walking along a metal railing with rufous-brown head and long rufous-tipped tail.

A Spectacled Parrotlet hanging upside down from a tree snag, peering curiously toward the camera.

A Bay-headed Tanager in profile showing the full spectrum from rufous crown through green mantle to blue rump.
A male Ruddy Ground Dove walking on cobblestones, rich rufous-brown body, gray head, and red eye in sharp detail.
A Yellow-bellied Elaenia perched on a bare branch, gray-olive plumage with slight crest and yellowish belly.
An Acorn Woodpecker on a lichen-covered branch showing its distinctive clown-like face, red crown, and pale eye.

A male Long-billed Starthroat with bill open, displaying iridescent purple gorget and blue crown.

A Guira Tanager glimpsed through branches, vivid orange breast partially obscured by foliage.
A Guira Tanager on a bare branch showing olive-gold upperparts with orange wing patches.
